{# Iteration-cycle phase: player names render via a {{#ifexist:}} chain so
   HBS players (current + historical) get a clickable link to their wiki page,
   while non-HBS players (opponents whose Hebrew name has no wiki page yet)
   appear as plain text. The chain checks mainspace first, then NS_DRAFT —
   so links work during the per-season review walk (everything in Draft:)
   and stay correct after promotion to mainspace. When an opposing player
   later signs for HBS and gets a wiki page created, all historic match
   mentions become live links automatically on next parser-cache invalidation.
   See docs/research/0003 §4 for the design discussion. #}
{% macro player_link(name) -%}
{%- if name -%}
{{"{{"}}#ifexist:{{ name }}|[[{{ name }}]]|{{"{{"}}#ifexist:Draft:{{ name }}|[[Draft:{{ name }}|{{ name }}]]|{{ name }}{{"}}"}}{{"}}"}}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
{# Resolve a lineup-entry value (string for legacy data, dict for new spider
   output) to its display name. Order matches apply_hebrew_mapping's write
   order: name_hebrew → name_english (which post-translate holds the Hebrew
   value for new entries) → name (legacy). #}
{% macro lineup_name(value) -%}
{%- if value is string -%}{{ value }}
{%- elif value is mapping -%}{{ value.name_hebrew or value.name_english or value.get('name', '') }}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
{{"{{"}}Match infobox
| competition = {{ match.competition or '' }}
| matchday = {{ match.matchday or '' }}
| date = {{ match.date or '' }}
| time = {{ match.time or '' }}
| venue = {{ match.venue or '' }}
| opponent = {{ match.opponent or '' }}
| result = {{ match.result or '' }}
| system_of_play = {{ match.system_of_play or '' }}
| attendance = {{ match.attendance or '' }}
{{"}}"}}

